reviewText: Not the best vintage "B" mystery movie...too much of the brash personalities of amateur detectives of the era...Protagonists run a bail bond agency. Not really a good buy.

This is a fun movie made in 1944 involving 2 bail bonds individuals, a presumed embezzler and murder.  The variety of characters in this movie is great as well as trying to figure out who the killer is.  I tend to like movies like this that provide me what I call true entertainment without profanity, sex or over the top violence (blood & guts) being displayed.  If a good script, good acting and a movie that doesn't need shocking sensationalism are for you, then I think you will enjoy this movie.
